<div id="left">
<h1>Welcome</h1>
<p>
<strong>OpenGuides</strong> is a network of free, community-maintained city guides
to which anyone can contribute.
</p>
<p>
<span class="red"><strong>News</strong></span><br>
May 9, 2004: <a
href="http://search.cpan.org/~kake/OpenGuides-0.31/">OpenGuides version
0.31 has been released</a>, including a number of improvements.
</p>
<p align="center">
<a href="http://www.perl.com/pub/a/2003/10/31/openguides.html"><img
src="img/openguides-perldotcom.gif" width="111" height="91" alt="perl.com - OpenGuides"
class="n"><br>
Read about us on perl.com!</a></strong>
</p>
<hr size="1" noshade>
<p>
<img src="/img/rdf_icon_small.png" width="24" height="26" alt="RDF"
align="right">
<strong>Our technical policy:</strong> to provide the maximum possible
amount of metadata about things in our guides in <a
href="http://www.w3.org/RDF/"><acronym title="Resource Description Framework">RDF</acronym></a>,
in order to facilitate integration into other systems.
</p>
<p>
&nbsp;
</p>
<p>
&nbsp;
</p>
